The '''''Encyclopedia of the Founders and Builders of Israel''''' is mainly a "[[Who's Who]]" [[Encyclopedia]] of the [[yishuv]] and the first 22 years of the [[state of Israel]]. The ''Encyclopedia'' was compiled and published by [[David Tidhar]] over 23 years and contains 19 volumes and about 6,000 [[biography|biographies]] of [[Jew]]ish leaders and settlers in [[Palestine (region)|Palestine]] from the 19th century up to the year 1970. [[Touro College]], together with the Tidhar family, established a [[website]] containing the ''Encyclopedia'' and made it freely available to the public.

==External links==
