The '''Imperial Ethiopian World Federation Incorporated Political Party''' is a [[political party]] in [[Jamaica]]. It was formed in 2002 by members of the [[Church of Haile Selassie I]], a [[Rastafari]] sect.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.jamaicans.com/culture/rasta/rasta_future.shtml|title = Rastafari's Future|date = May 20, 2003|publisher = Jamaicans.com}}</ref> It first contested national elections in [[Jamaican general election, 2002|2002]], when it received just 162 votes and failed to win a seat.<ref name=N1>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] (2005) ''Elections in the Americas: A data handbook, Volume I'', p433-435 {{ISBN|978-0-19-928357-6}}</ref> In the [[Jamaican general election, 2007|2007 elections]] it won only 192 votes and remained without parliamentary representation.

