 ("Year") *'''Ann.''' &ndash; ''Anni'' ("Years") *'''Ana''' &ndash; ''Antiphona'' *'''Ant.''' &ndash; ''Antiphona'' *'''Apost.''' &ndash; ''Apostolus'' ("Apostle") *'''Ap. Sed.''' &ndash; ''Apostolica Sedes'' ("Apostolic See") *'''Ap. Sed. Leg.''' &ndash; ''Apostolicæ Sedis Legatus'' ("Legate of the Apostolic See") *'''Archiep.''' &ndash; ''Archiepiscopus'' ("Archbishop") *'''Archid.''' &ndash; ''Archidiaconus'' ("Archdeacon") *'''Archiprb.''' &ndash; ''Archipresbyter'' ("Archpriest") *'''A.R.S.''' &ndash; ''Anno Reparatæ Salutis'' ("In the year of Our Redemption") *'''A.U.''' &ndash; ''Alma Urbs'' ("Beloved City" — i.e., Rome) *'''Authen.''' &ndash; ''Authentica'' ("Authentic" — e.g. letters) *'''Aux.''' &ndash; ''Auxilium, Auxilio'' ("Help", "With the help of") *'''A.D.''' &ndash; ''Ante Diem'' (e.g. in the phrase, "Ante Diem VI [or Sextum] Kal. Apriles", is equivalent to the sixth day before the Calends of April, counting both the Calends and the day intended to be indicated); or Anima Dulcis ("Sweet Soul") *'''A.Q.I.C.''' &ndash; ''Anima Quiescat In Christo'' ("May his [or her] Soul Repose in Christ")
==B== *'''B.''' &ndash; ''Balbius, Balbus, Beatus, Bene, Beneficiarius, Beneficium, Bonus, Brutus, Bustum.'' *'''B.''' (for '''V.''') &ndash; ''Berna Bivus, Bixit.'' *'''B.A.''' &ndash; ''Bixit anos, Bonis auguriis, Bonus amabilis.'' *'''BB., B.B.''' &ndash; ''Bene bene, i.e. optime, Optimus.'' *'''B.D.''' &ndash; ''Bonae deae, Bonum datum.'' *'''B.DD.''' &ndash; ''Bonis deabus.'' *'''B.D.S.M.''' &ndash; ''Bene de se merenti.'' *'''B.F.''' &ndash; ''Bona femina, Bona fides, Bona fortuna, Bonum factum.'' *'''B.F.''' &ndash; ''Bona femina, Bona filia.'' *'''B.H.''' &ndash; ''Bona hereditaria, Bonorum heres.'' *'''B.I.''' &ndash; ''Bonum judicium.'' *'''B.I.I.''' &ndash; ''Boni judicis judicium.'' *'''B.M.''' &ndash; ''Beatae memoriae, Bene merenti.'' *'''B.N.''' &ndash; ''Bona nostra, Bonum nomen.'' *'''BN.H.I.''' &ndash; ''Bona hic invenies.'' *'''B.P.''' &ndash; ''Bona paterna, Bonorum potestas, Bonum publicum.'' *'''B.Q.''' &ndash; ''Bene quiescat, Bona quaesita.'' *'''B.RP.N.''' &ndash; ''Boho reipublicae natus.'' *'''BRT.''' &ndash; ''Britannicus.'' *'''B.T.''' &ndash; ''Bonorum tutor, Brevi tempore.'' *'''B.V.''' &ndash; ''Bene vale, Bene vixit, Bonus vir.'' *'''B.V.V.''' &ndash; ''Balnea vina Venus.'' *'''BX.''' &ndash; ''Bixit'' (for ''vixit''). *'''B.''' &ndash; ''Balbius, Balbus, Beatus, Bene, Beneficiarius, Beneficium, Bonus, Brutus, Bustum.'' *'''B.''' (in loco '''V.''') &ndash; ''Berna Bivus, Bixit.'' *'''B.A.''' &ndash; ''Bixit annos'' [recte ''Vixit annos''], ''Bonis auguriis, Bonus amabilis.'' *'''BB., B.B.''' &ndash; ''Bene bene, i.e. optime, Optimus.'' *'''B.D.''' &ndash; ''Bonae deae, Bonum datum.'' *'''B.DD.''' &ndash; ''Bonis deabus.'' *'''B.D.S.M.''' &ndash; ''Bene de se merenti.'' *'''B.F.''' &ndash; ''Bona femina, Bona fides, Bona fortuna, Bonum factum.'' *'''B.F.''' &ndash; ''Bona femina, Bona filia.'' *'''B.H.''' &ndash; ''Bona hereditaria, Bonorum heres.'' *'''B.I.''' &ndash; ''Bonum iudicium.'' *'''B.I.I.''' &ndash; ''Boni iudicis iudicium.'' *'''B.M.''' &ndash; ''Beatae memoriae, Bene merenti.'' *'''B.M.V.''' &ndash; ''Beatae Mariae virginis'' *'''B.N.''' &ndash; ''Bona nostra, Bonum nomen.'' *'''BN.H.I.''' &ndash; ''Bona hic invenies.'' *'''B.P.''' &ndash; ''Bona paterna, Bonorum potestas, Bonum publicum.'' *'''B.Q.''' &ndash; ''Bene quiescat, Bona quaesita.'' *'''B.RP.N.''' &ndash; ''Boho reipublicae natus.'' *'''BRT.''' &ndash; ''Britannicus.'' *'''B.T.''' &ndash; ''Bonorum tutor, Brevi tempore.'' *'''B.V.''' &ndash; ''Bene vale, Bene vixit, Bonus vir.'' *'''B.V.V.''' &ndash; ''Balnea vina Venus.'' *'''BX.''' &ndash; ''Bixit'' [recte ''vixit'']. *'''B.''' &ndash; ''Bene Merenti'' *'''BMT.''' &ndash; ''Bene Merenti'' ("To the Well-Deserving") *'''B.M.''' &ndash; ''Bonae Memoriæ'' ("Of Happy Memory") *'''B.F.''' &ndash; ''Bonae Feminæ'' ("To the Good Woman") *'''B.I.C.''' &ndash; ''Bibas [for Vivas] In Christo'' ("May you Live In Christ") *'''B.M.F.''' &ndash; ''Bene Merenti Fecit'' ("He erected this to the Well-Deserving") *'''B.Q.''' &ndash; ''Bene Quiescat'' ("May he [or she] Rest Well") *'''B.A.''' &ndash; ''Baccalaureus Artium'' ("Bachelor of Arts") *'''B. BB.''' &ndash; ''Beatus, Beati'' ("Blessed") *'''B.C.''' &ndash; ''Before Christ'' *'''B.C.L.''' &ndash; ''Baccalaureus Civilis [or Canonicae] Legis'' ("Bachelor of Civil [or Canon] Law") *'''B.D.''' &ndash; ''Bachelor of Divinity'' *'''B.F.''' &ndash; ''Bona Fide'' ("In Good Faith") *'''Ben.''' &ndash; ''Benedictio'' ("Blessing") *'''Benevol.''' &ndash; ''Benevolentia'' ("Benevolence") *'''Bon. Mem.''' &ndash; ''Bonæ Memoriæ'' ("Of Happy Memory") *'''B.P.''' &ndash; ''Beatissime Pater'' ("Most Holy Father") *'''Bro.''' &ndash; ''Brother'' *'''B. Se.''' &ndash; ''Baccalaureus Scientiarum'' ("Bachelor of Sciences") *'''B.U.J.''' &ndash; ''Baccalaureus Utriusque Juris'' ("Bachelor of Both Laws" — i.e., civil and canon) *'''B.T.''' &ndash; ''Baccalaureus Theologiæ'' ("Bachelor of Theology") *'''B.V.''' &ndash; ''Beatitudo Vestra'' ("Your Holines