it'', ad caput litterarum. *'''S.P.Q.R.''' &ndash; ''[[SPQR|Senatus populusque Romanus]].'' *'''[[S. R. E.]]''' &ndash; ''[[Ecclesia Catholica Romana|Sacra vel Sancta Romana Ecclesia]]'' *'''S. R. I. (M. P.)''' &ndash; ''[[Imperium Romanum Sacrum|Sacrum Romanum Imperium]]'' *'''S.S.''' &ndash; ''Sancti, Sanctissimus, Sanctissimus senatus, Supra scripture.'' *'''SSS''' &ndash; ''Sanctissimus.'' *'''ST''' &ndash; ''Sanctus.'' *'''S.T.B.V.E.B.V.''' &ndash; ''Si Tu Bene Valeas Ego Bene Valeo.'' *'''STIP''' &ndash; ''Stipendorium.'' *'''STTL''' &ndash; ''Sit tibi terra levis.'' *'''S.V.B.E.E.Q.V.''' &ndash; ''Si vales bene est, ego quidem valeo.'' *'''S.''' &ndash; ''Sacrum'' *'''Sacr.''' &ndash; ''Sacrum'' ("Sacred") *'''Sab.''' &ndash; ''Sabbatum'' *'''Sabb.''' &ndash; ''Sabbatum'' ("Sabbath", Saturday) *'''Saec.''' &ndash; ''Saeculum'' (Century) *'''Sal.''' &ndash; ''Salus, Salutis'' ("Salvation", "of Salvation") *'''Salmant.''' &ndash; ''Salmanticenses'' (Theologians of Salamanca) *'''S.C.''' &ndash; ''Sacra Congregatio'' ("Sacred Congregation") *'''S.C.C.''' &ndash; ''Sacra Congregatio Concilii'' ("Sacred Congregation of the Council", i.e. of Trent) *'''S.C.EE.RR.''' &ndash; ''Sacra Congregatio Episcoporum et Regularium'' ("Sacred Congregation of Bishops and Regulars") *'''S.C.I.''' &ndash; ''Sacra Congregatio Indicis'' ("Sacred Congregation of the Index") *'''S.C.P.F.''' &ndash; ''Sacra Congregatio de Propaganda Fide'' ("Sacred Congregation for the Propagation of the Faith") *'''SCS''' &ndash; ''Sanctus'' ("Saint") *'''s.d.''' &ndash; ''sine data'' (undated book) *'''S.D.''' &ndash; ''Servus Dei'' (Servant of God) *'''Semid.''' &ndash; ''Semiduplex'' ("Semi" double feast — Breviary) *'''Septuag''' &ndash; ''Septuagesima'' ("Seventieth day" before Easter; always a Sunday — Breviary) *'''Sexag.''' &ndash; ''Sexagesima'' ("Sixtieth day" before Easter — Breviary) *'''Sig.''' &ndash; ''Sigillum'' ("Seal") *'''Simpl.''' &ndash; ''Simplex'' ("Simple" feast — Breviary) *''