The '''United Nations Audiovisual Library of International Law''' is a free online [[international law]] research and training tool. It was created and is maintained by the Codification Division of the [[United Nations Office of Legal Affairs]] as a part of its mandate under the United Nations Programme of Assistance in the Teaching, Study, Dissemination and Wider Appreciation of International Law.<ref>http://legal.un.org/avl/background.html</ref>
== Background == The United Nations Audiovisual Library of International Law was established in 2008<ref>[https://www.un.org/ga/search/view_doc.asp?symbol=a/res/62/62 General Assembly resolution 62/62]</ref> under the United Nations Programme of Assistance in the Teaching, Study, Dissemination and Wider Appreciation of International Law<ref>[https://www.un.org/ga/search/view_doc.asp?symbol=a/res/52/152 General Assembly resolution 52/152]</ref> as a tool for promoting knowledge of international law.
== Faculty == Over 240 international law experts from different regions, [[List of national legal systems|legal systems]] and sectors of the [[legal profession]] have recorded [[lectures]] for the Lecture Series, prepared introductory notes for the Historic Archives and contributed their [[Academic writing|scholarly writings]] to the Research Library.
Notable faculty members as of 1 July 2016:<ref>http://legal.un.org/avl/faculty.html</ref> {{div col|colwidth=15em}} * [[Georges Abi-Saab|Abi-Saab, Georges]] * [[Ronny Abraham|Abraham, Ronny]] * [[Awn Shawkat Al-Khasawneh|Al-Khasawneh, Awn S.]] * [[Kofi Annan|Annan, Kofi A.]] * [[M. Cherif Bassiouni|Bassiouni, M. Cherif]] * [[Mohamed Bennouna|Bennouna, Mohamed]] * [[Lea Brilmayer|Brilmayer, Lea]] * [[Thomas Buergenthal|Buergenthal, Thomas]] * [[Antônio Augusto Cançado Trindade|Cançado Trindade, Antônio Augusto]] * [[Antonio Cassese|Cassese, Antonio]] * [[David Caron|Caron, David]] * [[Hilary Charlesworth|Charlesworth, Hilary]] * [[Hans Corell|Corell, Hans]] * [[Philippe Couvreur|Couvreur, Philippe]] * [[David Crane (lawyer)|Crane, David M.]] * [[James Crawford (jurist)|Crawford, James]] * [[Joan Donoghue|Donoghue, Joan E.]] * [[John Dugard|Dugard, John]] * [[Benjamin B. Ferencz|Ferencz, Benjamin B.]] * [[Emmanuel Gaillard|Gaillard, Emmanuel]] * [[Giorgio Gaja|Gaja, Giorgio]] * [[Richard Goldstone|Goldstone, Richard]] * [[Guy Goodwin-Gill|Goodwin-Gill, Guy S.]] * [[Christopher Greenwood|Greenwood, Christopher]] * [[Christof Heyns|Heyns, Christof]] * [[Rosalyn Higgins|Higgins, Rosalyn]] * [[Kamal Hossain|Hossain, Kamal]] * [[Hassan Bubacar Jallow|Jallow, Hassan Bubacar]] * [[Walter Kälin|Kälin, Walter]] * [[Kenneth Keith|Keith, Kenneth]] * [[Benedict Kingsbury|Kingsbury, Benedict]] * [[Jan Klabbers|Klabbers, Jan]] * [[Harold Hongju Koh|Koh, Harold Hongju]] * [[Tommy Koh|Koh, Tommy]] * [[Santiago Oñate Laborde|Laborde, Santiago Oñate]] * [[Julio Lacarte Muró|Lacarte Muró, Julio]] * [[Pascal Lamy|Lamy, Pascal]] * [[Elihu Lauterpacht|Lauterpacht, Elihu]] * [[Menachem Mautner|Mautner, Menachem]] * [[Thomas Mayr-Harting|Mayr-Harting, Thomas]] * [[Myres S. McDougal|McDougal, Myres S.]] * [[Ted McWhinney|McWhinney, Edward]] * [[Theodor Meron|Meron, Theodor]] * [[Nicolas Michel|Michel, Nicolas]] * [[Jamshid Momtaz|Momtaz, Djamchid]] * [[Elizabeth Odio Benito|Odio Benito, Elizabeth]] * [[Hisashi Owada|Owada, Hisashi]] * [[Geoffrey Palmer (politician)|Palmer, Geoffrey]] * [[Jan Paulsson|Paulsson, Jan]] * [[Alain Pellet|Pellet, Alain]] * [[A. Rohan Perera|Perera, Rohan A.]] * [[Fausto Pocar|Pocar, Fausto]] * [[Nigel Rodley|Rodley, Nigel]] * [[Patrick Lipton Robinson|Robinson, Patrick]] * [[Christos Rozakis|Rozakis, Christos]] * [[Dan Sarooshi|Sarooshi, Dan]] * [[William Schabas|Schabas, William A.]] * [[Michael Scharf|Scharf, Michael]] * [[Stephen M. Schwebel|Schwebel, Stephen M.]] * [[Bernardo Sepúlveda Amor|Sepúlveda Amor, Bernardo]] * [[Malcolm Shaw|Shaw, Malcolm]] * [[Shi Jiuyong|Shi, Jiuyong]] * [[Bruno Simma|Simma, Bruno]] * [[Gerry Simpson|Simpson, Gerry]] * [[Song Sang-Hyun|Song, Sang Hyun]] * [[Dire Tladi|Tladi, Dire]] * [[Peter Tomka|Tomka, Peter]] * [[Christian Tomuschat|Tomuschat, Christian]] * [[Helmut Türk|Tuerk, Helmut]] * [[Brian Urquhart|Urquhart, Brian]] * [[Theo van Boven|van Boven, Theo]] * [[Albert Jan van den Berg|van den Berg, Albert Jan]] * [[Paul van Zyl|van Zyl, Paul]] * [[Stephen Vasciannie|Vasciannie, Stephen C.]] * [[Robin Vincent|Vincent, Robin]] * [[Ruth Wedgwood|Wedgwood, Ruth]] * [[Siegfried Wiessner|Wiessner, Siegfried]] * [[Elizabeth Wilmshurst|Wilmshurst, Elizabeth]] * [[Rüdiger Wolfrum|Wolfrum, Rüdiger]] * [[Michael Wood (lawyer)|Wood, Michael]] * [[Peter Woolcott|Woolcott, Peter]] * [[Xue Hanqin|Xue, Hanqin]] * [[Abdulqawi Yusuf|Yusuf, Abdulqawi A.]] {{div col end}}
== Description and contents == The Audiovisual Library is divided into three sections: the Historic Archives, the Lecture Series and the Research Library.<ref>https://www.un.org/law/avl/</ref> While the Library's main language is [[English language|English]], many lectures are in other languages ([[Arabic]], [[Chinese language|Chinese]], [[French language|French]], [[Russian language|Russian]] and [[Spanish language|Spanish]]) and all entries in the Historic Archives are translated into the six [[official languages of the United Nations]].
=== Historic archives === The Historic Archives provides detailed information on the negotiation process and significance of major international legal instruments. Each entry is accompanied by an introductory note prepared by an internationally recognized legal expert, a summary of the instrument's procedural history that led to its adoption and a list of all relevant preparatory documents. In some cases, audiovisual materials, including film footage, audio recordings and photos, of the negotiations<ref>E.g. the [[United Nations Charter|Charter of the United Nations]], the [[Universal Declaration of Human Rights]], the [[Genocide Convention]] and the U[[United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea|nited Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea]]</ref> are also available. The Historic Archives covers the following overarching subject areas:<ref>http://legal.un.org/avl/historicarchives.html</ref> {{div col|colwidth=15em}} * [[International criminal law|Criminal Law]] * [[Decolonization]] * Diplomatic and Consular Relations * [[Disarmament]] * [[Education]], [[Science]] and [[Culture]] * [[Environmental law]] * [[International health|Health]] * [[Human Rights]] * [[International economic law|International Economic Law]] * [[International Humanitarian Law]] * [[International Organization]]s * Law of [[International Relations]] * [[Space law|Law of Outer Space]] * [[Law of the Sea]] * Law of [[Treaties]] * [[Peace]] and [[Security]] * [[Refugee law|Refugees]] and [[Stateless Persons]] * [[Succession of states|Succession of States]] {{div col end}}
=== Lecture series === The Lecture series contains lectures recorded by members of the international legal community. Individuals who have participated in the Lecture Series include scholars, judges of international and regional judicial bodies, senior officials of international and regional organizations, and other international law practitioners. The themes covered by the Series are:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://legal.un.org/avl/lectureseries.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=July 9, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061112205146/http://www.icj-cij.org/icjwww/ipresscom/ipress2005/ipresscom2005-23_20051107.htm |archivedate=November 12, 2006 }}</ref> {{div col|colwidth=15em}} * [[Antarctica]] * [[Arctic]] * [[Arms Control]] and [[Disarmament]] * [[Boundary delimitation|Boundary Delimitation]] * [[Courts]] and [[Tribunals]] * [[Criminal Law]] and [[Criminal procedure|Procedure]] * [[Cultural Heritage]] * [[Right to development|Development]] * Diplomatic and Consular Relations * [[Diplomatic Protection]] * [[Emergency management|Disaster Prevention and Relief]] * [[Environmental Law]] * [[Health]] and [[Science]] * [[Human Rights]] * [[Human Security]] * International [[Civil Aviation]] * [[International economic law|International Economic Law]] * [[International Labour Law]] * [[International Law]] * International [[Migration (human)|Migration]] Law * [[International Organizations]] * International [[Watercourse]]s * [[Law of Armed Conflict]] * [[Space law|Law of Outer Space]] * [[Law of the Sea]] * Law of [[Treaties]] * [[Peace]] and [[Security]] * [[Dispute resolution|Peaceful Settlement of Disputes]] * [[Regional Organizations]] * [[Rule of Law]], [[Democracy]] and [[Good Governance]] * [[List of specialized agencies of the United Nations|Specialized Agencies and Related Organizations]] * [[Sovereign state|States]] * [[United Nations]] {{div col end}}
=== Research Library === The Research Library consists of an extensive online catalog of [[international law]] materials. The Library provides links to online collections of [[treaties]], [[jurisprudence]] of [[courts]] and [[tribunals]], official publications and documents of the [[United Nations]] and related [[international organizations]], [[Academic writing|scholarly writings]] and other research materials including international [[law journals]] and [[yearbooks]], as well as other training materials.
